## Functions

### areLoadsReorderable() {#ac01b3bf4dda9266ec05d70b2f55281fa}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool areLoadsReorderable (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/loadinst">LoadInst</a> &#42; Use, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/loadinst">LoadInst</a> &#42; MayClobber)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
This does one-way checks to see if <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a> could theoretically be hoisted above MayClobber.

This will not check the other way around.

This assumes that, for the purposes of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryssa">MemorySSA</a>, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a> comes directly after MayClobber, with no potentially clobbering operations in between them. (Where potentially clobbering ops are memory barriers, aliased stores, etc.)

Definition at line <a href="#l00256">256</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/memoryssa-cpp">MemorySSA.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### checkClobberSanity() {#a930e3a524f031bdb14fe281e4eff4219}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static LLVM&#95;ATTRIBUTE&#95;UNUSED void checkClobberSanity (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42; Start, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42; ClobberAt, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorylocation">MemoryLocation</a> &amp; StartLoc, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryssa">MemorySSA</a> &amp; MSSA, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> UpwardsMemoryQuery &amp; Query, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/batchaaresults">BatchAAResults</a> &amp; AA, bool AllowImpreciseClobber=false)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Verifies that <code>Start</code> is clobbered by <code>ClobberAt</code>, and that nothing inbetween <code>Start</code> and <code>ClobberAt</code> can clobbers <code>Start</code>.

This is meant to be as simple and self-contained as possible. Because it uses no cache, etc., it can be relatively expensive.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Start">The <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> that we want to walk from.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="ClobberAt">A clobber for Start.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="StartLoc">The <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorylocation">MemoryLocation</a> for Start.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="MSSA">The <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryssa">MemorySSA</a> instance that Start and ClobberAt belong to.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Query">The <a href="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-memoryssa-cpp-/upwardsmemoryquery">UpwardsMemoryQuery</a> we used for our search.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="<a href=&quot;/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/aa&quot;>AA</a>">The <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ae457f1cf451ed893666c4a384e58f8e5">AliasAnalysis</a> we used for our search.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="AllowImpreciseClobber">Always false, unless we do relaxed verify.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00250" /><CodeLine lineNumber="250"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This does one-way checks to see if Use could theoretically be hoisted above</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00251" /><CodeLine lineNumber="251"><Highlight kind="comment">/// MayClobber. This will not check the other way around.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00252" /><CodeLine lineNumber="252"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00253" /><CodeLine lineNumber="253"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This assumes that, for the purposes of MemorySSA, Use comes directly after</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00751" /><CodeLine lineNumber="751"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Try to optimize a phi as best as we can. Returns a SmallVector of Paths</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00752" /><CodeLine lineNumber="752"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// that act as legal clobbers. Note that this won&#39;t return &#42;all&#42; clobbers.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00753" /><CodeLine lineNumber="753"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00754" /><CodeLine lineNumber="754"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Phi optimization algorithm tl;dr:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00755" /><CodeLine lineNumber="755"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   - Find the earliest def/phi, A, we can optimize to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00756" /><CodeLine lineNumber="756"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   - Find if all paths from the starting memory access ultimately reach A</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00757" /><CodeLine lineNumber="757"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///     - If not, optimization isn&#39;t possible.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00758" /><CodeLine lineNumber="758"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///     - Otherwise, walk from A to another clobber or phi, A&#39;.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00759" /><CodeLine lineNumber="759"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///       - If A&#39; is a def, we&#39;re done.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00760" /><CodeLine lineNumber="760"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///       - If A&#39; is a phi, try to optimize it.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// A path is a series of &#123;MemoryAccess, MemoryLocation&#125; pairs. A path</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// terminates when a MemoryAccess that clobbers said MemoryLocation is found.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><Highlight kind="normal">  OptznResult tryOptimizePhi(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryphi">MemoryPhi</a> &#42;Phi, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42;Start,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"><Highlight kind="normal">                             </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorylocation">MemoryLocation</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/loc">Loc</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00824" /><CodeLine lineNumber="824"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    above this phi, whereas the other can. If we cache the second path</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00825" /><CodeLine lineNumber="825"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    back, we&#39;ll end up with suboptimal cache entries. We can handle</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00826" /><CodeLine lineNumber="826"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    cases like this a bit better when we either try to find all</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00827" /><CodeLine lineNumber="827"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    clobbers that block phi optimization, or when our cache starts</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00828" /><CodeLine lineNumber="828"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    supporting unfinished searches.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00829" /><CodeLine lineNumber="829"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// B. We can&#39;t reliably cache TerminatedPaths back here without doing</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00830" /><CodeLine lineNumber="830"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    extra checks; consider a case like:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00831" /><CodeLine lineNumber="831"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//       T</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00832" /><CodeLine lineNumber="832"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      / \\</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00833" /><CodeLine lineNumber="833"><Highlight kind="comment">        //     D   C</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00834" /><CodeLine lineNumber="834"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      \\ /</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00835" /><CodeLine lineNumber="835"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//       S</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00836" /><CodeLine lineNumber="836"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    Where T is our target, C is a node with a clobber on it, D is a</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00837" /><CodeLine lineNumber="837"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    diamond (with a clobber &#42;only&#42; on the left or right node, N), and</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00838" /><CodeLine lineNumber="838"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    S is our start. Say we walk to D, through the node opposite N</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00839" /><CodeLine lineNumber="839"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    (read: ignoring the clobber), and see a cache entry in the top</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00840" /><CodeLine lineNumber="840"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    node of D. That cache entry gets put into TerminatedPaths. We then</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00841" /><CodeLine lineNumber="841"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    walk up to C (N is later in our worklist), find the clobber, and</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00842" /><CodeLine lineNumber="842"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    quit. If we append TerminatedPaths to OtherClobbers, we&#39;ll cache</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00843" /><CodeLine lineNumber="843"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    the bottom part of D to the cached clobber, ignoring the clobber</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00844" /><CodeLine lineNumber="844"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    in N. Again, this problem goes away if we start tracking all</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00845" /><CodeLine lineNumber="845"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    blockers for a given phi optimization.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00846" /><CodeLine lineNumber="846"><Highlight kind="normal">        TerminatedPath Result&#123;CurNode.Last, defPathIndex(CurNode)&#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00847" /><CodeLine lineNumber="847"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#123;Result, &#123;&#125;&#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00848" /><CodeLine lineNumber="848"><Highlight kind="normal">      &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00849" /><CodeLine lineNumber="849"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00850" /><CodeLine lineNumber="850"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If there&#39;s nothing left to search, then all paths led to valid clobbers</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00851" /><CodeLine lineNumber="851"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// that we got from our cache; pick the nearest to the start, and allow</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00852" /><CodeLine lineNumber="852"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the rest to be cached back.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00853" /><CodeLine lineNumber="853"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (NewPaused.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatecommon/#ad9a3c7bc26b130377bbafc170b5f88a2">empty</a>()) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00854" /><CodeLine lineNumber="854"><Highlight kind="normal">        MoveDominatedPathToEnd(TerminatedPaths);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00855" /><CodeLine lineNumber="855"><Highlight kind="normal">        TerminatedPath Result = TerminatedPaths.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl/#a0c8ffe664a36e30d49c84d0aded2fe08">pop&#95;back&#95;val</a>();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00856" /><CodeLine lineNumber="856"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#123;Result, std::move(TerminatedPaths)&#125;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00857" /><CodeLine lineNumber="857"><Highlight kind="normal">      &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00858" /><CodeLine lineNumber="858"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00859" /><CodeLine lineNumber="859"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42;DefChainEnd = </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">nullptr</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00860" /><CodeLine lineNumber="860"><Highlight kind="normal">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;TerminatedPath, 4&gt;</a> Clobbers;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00861" /><CodeLine lineNumber="861"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (ListIndex Paused : NewPaused) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00862" /><CodeLine lineNumber="862"><Highlight kind="normal">        UpwardsWalkResult WR = walkToPhiOrClobber(Paths&#91;Paused&#93;);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00863" /><CodeLine lineNumber="863"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (WR.IsKnownClobber)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00864" /><CodeLine lineNumber="864"><Highlight kind="normal">          Clobbers.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatebase/#af42bfbc067df27c19ee2fc859df58799">push&#95;back</a>(&#123;WR.Result, Paused&#125;);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00865" /><CodeLine lineNumber="865"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">else</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00868" /><CodeLine lineNumber="868"><Highlight kind="normal">      &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00870" /><CodeLine lineNumber="870"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (!TerminatedPaths.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatecommon/#ad9a3c7bc26b130377bbafc170b5f88a2">empty</a>()) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00871" /><CodeLine lineNumber="871"><Highlight kind="normal">        </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If we couldn&#39;t find the dominating phi/liveOnEntry in the above loop,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00928" /><CodeLine lineNumber="928"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Finds the nearest clobber for the given query, optimizing phis if</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00929" /><CodeLine lineNumber="929"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// possible.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00930" /><CodeLine lineNumber="930" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-memoryssa-cpp-/clobberwalker/#ac58172a7cb0dff9ad4908bfd8fc07685"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-memoryssa-cpp-/clobberwalker/#ac58172a7cb0dff9ad4908bfd8fc07685">findClobber</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/batchaaresults">BatchAAResults</a> &amp;BAA, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42;Start,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00931" /><CodeLine lineNumber="931"><Highlight kind="normal">                            <a href="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-memoryssa-cpp-/upwardsmemoryquery">UpwardsMemoryQuery</a> &amp;Q, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &amp;UpWalkLimit) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00932" /><CodeLine lineNumber="932"><Highlight kind="normal">    AA = &amp;BAA;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00934" /><CodeLine lineNumber="934"><Highlight kind="normal">    UpwardWalkLimit = &amp;UpWalkLimit;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00935" /><CodeLine lineNumber="935"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Starting limit must be &gt; 0</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00936" /><CodeLine lineNumber="936"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (!UpWalkLimit)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00937" /><CodeLine lineNumber="937"><Highlight kind="normal">      UpWalkLimit++;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00938" /><CodeLine lineNumber="938"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00939" /><CodeLine lineNumber="939"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42;Current = Start;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00940" /><CodeLine lineNumber="940"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This walker pretends uses don&#39;t exist. If we&#39;re handed one, silently grab</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00942" /><CodeLine lineNumber="942"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &#42;MU = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a22eeee01734061ac1b31ccd994c49eef">dyn&#95;cast&lt;MemoryUse&gt;</a>(Start))</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00945" /><CodeLine lineNumber="945"><Highlight kind="normal">    DefPath FirstDesc(Q.<a href="/docs/api/structs/anonymous-namespace-memoryssa-cpp-/upwardsmemoryquery/#abded55036bcd9780f67503c3e6994914">StartingLoc</a>, Current, Current, std::nullopt);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00946" /><CodeLine lineNumber="946"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Fast path for the overly-common case (no crazy phi optimization</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00947" /><CodeLine lineNumber="947"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// necessary)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00948" /><CodeLine lineNumber="948"><Highlight kind="normal">    UpwardsWalkResult WalkResult = walkToPhiOrClobber(FirstDesc);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00949" /><CodeLine lineNumber="949"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42;Result;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00950" /><CodeLine lineNumber="950"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (WalkResult.IsKnownClobber) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00951" /><CodeLine lineNumber="951"><Highlight kind="normal">      Result = WalkResult.Result;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1297"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This class is a batch walker of all MemoryUse&#39;s in the program, and points</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1298"><Highlight kind="comment">/// their defining access at the thing that actually clobbers them.  Because it</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1299"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is a batch walker that touches everything, it does not operate like the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1300"><Highlight kind="comment">/// other walkers.  This walker is basically performing a top-down SSA renaming</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01301" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1301"><Highlight kind="comment">/// pass, where the version stack is used as the cache.  This enables it to be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1302"><Highlight kind="comment">/// significantly more time and memory efficient than using the regular walker,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01303" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1303"><Highlight kind="comment">/// which is walking bottom-up.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1342"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Optimize the uses in a given block This is basically the SSA renaming</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1343"><Highlight kind="comment">/// algorithm, with one caveat: We are able to use a single stack for all</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1344"><Highlight kind="comment">/// MemoryUses.  This is because the set of &#42;possible&#42; reaching MemoryDefs is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1345"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the same for every MemoryUse.  The &#42;actual&#42; clobbering MemoryDef is just</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1346"><Highlight kind="comment">/// going to be some position in that stack of possible ones.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1347"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1348"><Highlight kind="comment">/// We track the stack positions that each MemoryLocation needs</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1350"><Highlight kind="comment">/// things that changed since last time.  The same MemoryLocation should</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1351"><Highlight kind="comment">/// get clobbered by the same store (getModRefInfo does not use invariantness or</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1352"><Highlight kind="comment">/// things like this, and if they start, we can modify MemoryLocOrCall to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1353"><Highlight kind="comment">/// include relevant data)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1401"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// XXX: This is non-optimal, but only is slower cases with heavily</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
